==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|indolent|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|indolentem|lang=la}}, from {{term|in-||not|lang=la}} + {{term/t|la|dolēns||pain}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɪn.dəl.ənt/}}
* {{audio|en-us-indolent.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# [[habitually|Habitually]] [[lazy]], [[procrastinate|procrastinating]], or resistant to physical labor/labour.
#: ''The '''indolent''' girl resisted doing her homework.''
# [[induce|Inducing]] [[laziness]] (e.g. '''''indolent''' comfort'').
# {{context|medicine|lang=en}} Causing [[scant]] or no physical pain; progressing slowly; inactive (of an [[ulcer]], etc.).
# {{context|medicine|lang=en}} Healing slowly.

